put the acid on
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:[AND 1906: possibly f. acid test of gold.] to make a sharp (or final) demand on; to put the bite, juice on (a person for money, favours, etc). Cf. hard word.
Origin:[none]
Register: informal
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
